Dark Mode & Theme Toggle Walkthrough
I have successfully fixed the dark mode issues on the Dashboard and implemented a theme toggle for better user control.

Changes
1. Theme Toggle
Added a new 
ThemeToggle
 component to the top navigation bar. You can now easily switch between Light, Dark, and System themes.

cycled via a sun/moon icon button in the header.
2. Dashboard Dark Mode
The Dashboard page (/dashboard) was previously hardcoded to white. I updated it to use theme-aware colors:

Background adapts to theme (Dark/Light).
Text colors adjust automatically for readability.
Cards and charts now look consistent in both modes.
4. Chat Input Visibility
Fixed an issue where the chat input text was unreadable in dark mode.

Added dark:prose-invert to the text editor to ensure proper typography contrast in dark mode.
5. Sent Message Visibility
Fixed an issue where sent message bubbles were white/invisible in dark mode due to undefined custom classes.

Replaced bg-container and bg-backdrop with standard bg-muted and hover:bg-muted/80.
6. Chat Persistence
Fixed an issue where chat history was lost when navigating between pages (e.g., to Settings and back).

Lifted 
TamboProvider
 to 
src/app/layout.tsx
 to maintain state globally.
Created 
TamboProviderWrapper
 to handle client-side configuration.
